article.headline: Sam Houston St. 89, Texas-San Antonio 86
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Corey Allmond hit two free throws with six seconds left to give Sam Houston State an 89-86 double-overtime victory over Texas-San Antonio on Wednesday night. UTSA's Morris Smith IV missed a chance to tie it with a 3-pointer in the closing seconds. Allmond and Barkley Falkner each scored 22 points for Sam Houston State (12-8, 6-1 Southland). Falkner hit a layup as time expired to tie the game at 79-79 at the end of the first overtime. Omar Johnson led UTSA with 18 points, including the layup that sent the game into overtime tied at 69-69. Lance Pevehouse scored 14 points for Sam Houston State. Smith and Chris Allen each scored 15 points for UTSA (13-7, 4-3). Travis Gabbidon, Demarco Stepter and Josh Bonney each had 10.
